Who Stole My Life?

Every 3 seconds an American's identity is stolen. Just how safe is your 401k? Your bank account? Your home? Your credit? Crime Reporter Tom Morris Jr. investigates the identity theft epidemic. Find out how you can help protect yourself with LifeLock.

CSI: NY Grand Murder at Central Station

Mac and Hawkes discover that a murdered plastic surgeon had many patients suing him for millions of dollars.

CSI: NY Zoo York

The investigators look into the death of a man who was thrown to the tigers at the Bronx Zoo.

CSI: NY Sleight Out of Hand

The team wonders if the tricks of a world-renowned illusionist (Criss Angel) have become reality when two of his crew members are found dead in ways that mimic his illusions.

CSI: NY Buzzkill

The team investigates when a supermodel is found dead in a giant martini glass on a billboard in Times Square.

CSI: NY LAT 40 Degrees 47 Minutes N/Long 73 Degrees 58 Minutes W

Mac and the team follow the trail of evidence left by a killer after two bodies are found, one at the north end of the city, the other at the south.

CSI: NY Unwrapped

The team goes to a housing project in Brooklyn, N.Y., to investigate the murder of a successful businessman.

CSI: NY Nine Thirteen

The team investigates when a masked man is found at the bottom of a skyscraper with a history of mysterious deaths.

Law & Order: Criminal Intent Malignant

Detectives Goren and Eames bring to light a crime involving a pharmaceutical supplier who has been tampering with cancer-fighting drugs.

Law & Order: Criminal Intent Tomorrow

Detectives investigate the murder of the children of a wealthy man, suspecting first the stepmother, then the nannies.
